{"build_type":"executable","description":"Measurement spike for the lossless-compression decision (user stance: never truncate a body; if it is too big, represent it more efficiently). stdin=IPM package. Emits {verbose_bytes, concise_bytes, saved_pct_x100} where verbose_bytes = minified-JSON length of the package's function_definitions as-is (what op.read returns today), concise_bytes = minified-JSON length of the SAME functions run through the existing concise lens vw_all_functions (full fidelity, round-trippable via expand). Quantifies how much the concise representation saves without dropping any information, so the concise-as-payload direction is decided by data not assumption. Reuses vw_all_functions, render_document_value_producing_cstring, compute_string_length_by_scanning, finalize_reader_response_envelope.","module_name":"measure-concise-versus-verbose-octet-sizes","package_name":"measure-concise-versus-verbose-octet-sizes","function_definitions":{"measure-concise-versus-verbose-octet-sizes":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"hundred","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":100},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_fd","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"function_definitions"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_verbose","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"verbose_bytes"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_concise","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"concise_bytes"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","vari